  Summary:
  Scenario A: E and f BOTH fully recovered — near-boundary is REVERSIBLE.
  Scenario B: E offset = +2 deterministically (floor absorbs 2 down-steps);
              f = 0 regardless of original — floor DESTROYS fraction.
  Recovery classification:
    Near-boundary    → FULLY RECOVERABLE
    Through-floor    → E PARTIALLY RECOVERABLE (deterministic +2 offset),
                       f IRRECOVERABLE (permanent zero)

